the mission to retrieve Mark
Watney will be a success.

1558
01:52:36,280 --> 01:52:38,078
<i>They've had
some contact with him,</i>

1559
01:52:38,160 --> 01:52:40,117
<i>but it hasn't been very much.</i>

1560
01:52:40,200 --> 01:52:41,520
<i>We have to remind our viewers</i>

1561
01:52:41,600 --> 01:52:43,273
<i>that we're watching this
as it unfolds.</i>

1562
01:52:43,480 --> 01:52:45,233
<i>So we'll try
and keep you up-to-date</i>

1563
01:52:45,360 --> 01:52:47,192
<i>as to what exactly is going on.</i>

1564
01:52:47,400 --> 01:52:51,030
<i>Let's listen in to NASA making
contact with Mark Watney.</i>

1565
01:52:51,240 --> 01:52:52,435
<i>Let's listen in.</i>

1566
01:52:59,120 --> 01:53:01,396
If something goes wrong,
what can Mission Control do?

1567
01:53:01,840 --> 01:53:03,957
Not a damn thing.

1568
01:53:04,480 --> 01:53:06,278
It's all happening
12 light-minutes away...

1569
01:53:06,440 --> 01:53:08,113
which means it takes
24 minutes for them

1570
01:53:08,200 --> 01:53:10,157
to get the answer to any
question they ask.

1571
01:53:11,280 --> 01:53:13,317
The whole launch
is 12 minutes...

1572
01:53:15,040 --> 01:53:16,679
so they're on their own.

1573
01:54:21,880 --> 01:54:22,880
<i>...just how long
Mark has been</i>

1574
01:54:23,000 --> 01:54:24,070
<i>completely alone on Mars.</i>

1575
01:54:24,160 --> 01:54:27,119
<i>We're talking to a psychology
expert later to discuss...</i>

1576
01:54:49,880 --> 01:54:51,473
<i>Fuel pressure, green.</i>

1577
01:54:51,840 --> 01:54:53,991
Engine alignment, perfect.

1578
01:54:54,160 --> 01:54:55,435
<i>Communications, five by five.</i>

1579
01:54:57,200 --> 01:54:59,954
<i>We are ready for pre-flight
checklist, Commander.</i>

1580
01:55:00,160 --> 01:55:02,720
<i>Mission Control,
this is</i> Hermes <i>actual.</i>

1581
01:55:02,800 --> 01:55:04,792
<i>We will proceed on schedule.</i>

1582
01:55:05,000 --> 01:55:06,992
<i>We are T-minus 2 minutes,
10 seconds</i>

1583
01:55:07,080 --> 01:55:08,480
<i>to launch, by the mark.</i>

1584
01:55:09,720 --> 01:55:10,720
About two minutes, Watney.

1585
01:55:10,920 --> 01:55:11,990
<i>How you doing down there?</i>

1586
01:55:12,160 --> 01:55:13,355
I'm good.

1587
01:55:14,200 --> 01:55:15,998
I'm anxious to get up to you.

1588
01:55:16,520 --> 01:55:17,874
Thanks for coming back for me.

1589
01:55:17,960 --> 01:55:18,960
<i>Well, we're on it.</i>

1590
01:55:19,120 --> 01:55:20,839
<i>Remember, you'll be pulling
some serious G's,</i>

1591
01:55:20,920 --> 01:55:22,593
<i>so it's okay to pass out.</i>

1592
01:55:22,760 --> 01:55:24,717
You're in Martinez's hands now.

1593
