1646
01:57:47,760 --> 01:57:49,160
<i>with the transmission.</i>

1647
01:57:56,320 --> 01:57:57,879
<i>I have interval pings.</i>

1648
01:57:58,040 --> 01:58:00,077
Intercept velocity will be
11 meters per second.

1649
01:58:00,240 --> 01:58:01,993
I can make that work.

1650
01:58:02,600 --> 01:58:04,956
Distance at intercept will be...

1651
01:58:05,400 --> 01:58:07,073
We'll be 68 kilometers apart.

1652
01:58:07,520 --> 01:58:09,318
<i>68 kilometers?</i>

1653
01:58:09,560 --> 01:58:11,995
<i>Did she just say 68 kilometers?</i>

1654
01:58:12,760 --> 01:58:13,760
Come on, guys, keep it together.

1655
01:58:13,840 --> 01:58:14,876
Work the problem.

1656
01:58:15,560 --> 01:58:17,153
Johanssen, time to intercept?

1657
01:58:17,840 --> 01:58:19,832
<i>39 minutes, 12 seconds.</i>

1658
01:58:20,520 --> 01:58:22,000
Martinez, what if we
point our thrusters

1659
01:58:22,080 --> 01:58:23,230
in the same direction?

1660
01:58:23,680 --> 01:58:26,639
Well, it depends how much fuel
you wanna save...

1661
01:58:26,800 --> 01:58:28,154
for the altitude adjustments
for the trip home.

1662
01:58:28,320 --> 01:58:29,390
How much do you need?

1663
01:58:29,560 --> 01:58:33,839
I can get by with about 20%
of what we have left.

1664
01:58:34,920 --> 01:58:38,152
If we use 75.5% of remaining
altitude-adjust fuel...

1665
01:58:38,320 --> 01:58:40,198
that will bring the intercept
range to zero.

1666
01:58:40,320 --> 01:58:41,320
Do it.

1667
01:58:42,240 --> 01:58:45,358
Hang on. It brings
the range to zero...

1668
01:58:45,520 --> 01:58:48,240
but the intercept velocity
will be 42 meters per second.

1669
01:58:48,400 --> 01:58:50,039
<i>And that's way too fast.</i>

1670
01:58:50,440 --> 01:58:52,432
Then we'll have 39 minutes
to figure out

1671
01:58:52,560 --> 01:58:54,074
how to slow down.

1672
01:58:57,160 --> 01:58:58,913
Martinez, burn the jets.

1673
01:58:59,080 --> 01:59:00,480
Copy that.

1674
01:59:22,920 --> 01:59:24,957
MAV to <i>Hermes.</i>

1675
01:59:25,040 --> 01:59:26,040
<i>Watney?</i>

1676
01:59:26,160 --> 01:59:27,160
<i>Affirmative.</i>

1677
01:59:31,200 --> 01:59:32,634
<i>What's your status?</i>

1678
01:59:33,000 --> 01:59:34,514
<i>My chest hurts.</i>

1679
01:59:35,040 --> 01:59:36,394
<i>I broke my ribs.</i>

1680
01:59:37,240 --> 01:59:38,310
<i>How are you?</i>

1681
01:59:38,520 --> 01:59:39,590
<i>We're working on getting to you.</i>

1682
01:59:39,680 --> 01:59:41,160
<i>There was a complication
during launch.</i>

1683
01:59:41,360 --> 01:59:42,714
Copy that.

1684
01:59:43,280 --> 01:59:44,714
How bad is it?

1685
01:59:44,880 --> 01:59:46,439
<i>We've corrected
the intercept range,</i>

1686
01:59:46,520 --> 01:59:48,477
<i>but we've got a problem
with intercept velocity.</i>

1687
01:59:48,640 --> 01:59:49,915
<i>How big a problem?</i>

1688
01:59:50,120 --> 01:59:51,600
42 meters a second.

1689
01:59:51,960 --> 01:59:52,960
Well...

1690
01:59:54,280 --> 01:59:55,714
shit.

1691
02:00:00,640 --> 02:00:02,438
<i>Commander, I have an idea.</i>

1692
02:00:02,600 --> 02:00:04,034
<i>Go ahead, Mark.</i>

1693
02:00:04,200 --> 02:00:07,352
Well, if I can find
something sharp in here...

1694
02:00:07,520 --> 02:00:10,354
and poke a hole in the glove
of my EVA suit...

1695
02:00:10,520 --> 02:00:12,989
I could use the escaping air
as a thruster...

1696
02:00:13,160 --> 02:00:14,560
<i>and fly towards you.</i>

1697
02:00:14,720 --> 02:00:17,758
<i>It would be easy to control
because it would be on my arm.</i>

1698
02:00:18,040 --> 02:00:19,872
I can't see you having
any control if you did that.

1699
02:00:20,040 --> 02:00:21,838
You'd be eyeballing
the intercept

1700
02:00:21,920 --> 02:00:24,196
using a thrust vector
you can barely control.

1701
02:00:24,440 --> 02:00:27,592
Yes, those are all
very good points.

1702
02:00:28,400 --> 02:00:31,154
But consider this.

1703
02:00:33,200 --> 02:00:35,840
I'd get to fly around
like Iron Man.

1704
02:00:37,160 --> 02:00:38,719
<i>Commander...</i>

1705
02:00:38,880 --> 02:00:40,553
<i>let's go Iron Man.</i>

1706
02:00:43,640 --> 02:00:44,915
<i>This is unexpected LOS.</i>

1707
02:00:45,160 --> 02:00:47,038
<i>Communication lost. Stand by.</i>

1708
02:00:48,080 --> 02:00:50,720
Maybe it's not the worst idea.

1709
02:00:50,880 --> 02:00:52,712
No, it is the worst idea.
It's the worst idea ever.

1710
02:00:52,880 --> 02:00:53,996
Not what he said.

1711
02:00:54,160 --> 02:00:56,277
Using atmosphere as thrust.

1712
02:00:58,520 --> 02:01:00,432
What happens if we blow the VAL?

1713
02:01:00,720 --> 02:01:02,518
Wait, you want to open
the vehicular airlock?

1714
02:01:02,760 --> 02:01:03,830
It'll give us a good kick.

1715
02:01:04,000 --> 02:01:05,753
But also blow
the nose off the ship.

1716
02:01:05,920 --> 02:01:08,719
And all the air would leave
and we need air to not die.

1717
02:01:08,880 --> 02:01:11,111
We would seal the bridge
and the reactor room.

1718
02:01:11,320 --> 02:01:12,549
Everywhere else would go vacuo.

1719
02:01:13,200 --> 02:01:14,200
Vogel.

1720
02:01:14,280 --> 02:01:15,555
<i>Go ahead, Commander.</i>

1721
02:01:15,960 --> 02:01:18,600
I need you to come inside
and make a... bomb.

1722
02:01:19,360 --> 02:01:20,360
Again, Commander?

